{meta: artist Billy Joe Royal}
{meta: composer Wyatt Easterling, Don Goodman,}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]If the jukebox took teardrops I'd [C]dance all night long
I'd [D7]sail away to yesterday on the [C]wings of a [G]song
I'd close my eyes then hold you tight till the [C]blue light of dawn
If the jukebox took [G]teardrops [D7]I'd cry all night [G]long
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
My [C]baby's gone she left today
[G]And I got a feeling she's gone to stay
She [C]said she needed money so I took out a loan
[A7]Now both my little honey and my money are [D7]gone
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[G]If the jukebox took teardrops it [C]would play a hurting song
If the [D7]jukebox took teardrops I'd [C]cry all night [G]long
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
